dct_alternative_sm: Sheet IV West Coast of India from Kundari to Boria Pagoda
dct_description_sm: Surveyed by Lieuts: R. Williams & E.L. Seaton. I.N. assisted by F.B. Girdlestone & F.W.T. Willaume I.N. 1861 ; ...under the Superintendence of Captn. G.H. Richards. R.N., F.R.S. Hydrographer ; Engraved by E. Stanford ; the Outer Soundings are principally from the Chart of 1850 by Lieutts. W.B. Selby & R.W. Whish I.N.
Depths shown by soundings and lines; relief by hachures and spot heights
Shows coasts, shoals, reefs, drainage, coastal topography and vegetation, farmland, buildings
